  "What does 'climate attribution' mean?": "",
  "The precise measurement of atmospheric temperature at multiple altitude levels using weather balloons, satellites, and ground stations": "",
  "The legal and regulatory process of assigning financial responsibility for environmental pollution damages to specific industrial sources": "",
  "The operational meteorological process of predicting short-term weather conditions for the next day or two using atmospheric models": "",
  "The scientific process of determining whether and how much human-caused climate change contributed to a specific weather event": "",
  "Attribution science uses statistical methods and climate models to determine the extent to which human-caused warming made a specific extreme event more likely or more intense.": "",
  "What is permafrost thaw?": "",
