  "The annual summer melting of floating sea ice in the Arctic Ocean that exposes open water before refreezing during the winter season": "",
  "The springtime breakup and thawing of frozen river and lake ice surfaces that restores water flow and allows navigation in the north": "",
  "The melting of permanently frozen ground due to rising temperatures, which releases stored greenhouse gases and destabilizes infrastructure": "",
  "Permafrost thaw is the melting of previously permanently frozen ground due to warming, releasing stored methane and CO₂ and creating a dangerous positive feedback loop.": "",
  "What is the global temperature anomaly?": "",
  "The temperature difference between day and night": "",
  "An unusual weather event": "",
  "The difference between a measured temperature and a long-term average baseline, used to track warming trends": "",
  "The exact global temperature in degrees Celsius": "",
  "Temperature anomaly measures departure from a baseline average (usually 1951-1980), making it easier to detect warming trends regardless of regional temperature differences.": "",
  "What does 'ice sheet mass balance' mean?": "",
