  "The average thickness of floating sea ice measured at the geographic North Pole using submarine sonar instruments and satellite altimetry": "",
  "Ice sheet mass balance compares annual snowfall (gain) with melting and iceberg calving (loss); both Greenland and Antarctic ice sheets currently have negative mass balance, meaning they are shrinking.": "",
