  "Because pH is logarithmic, a 0.1 decrease represents a 30% increase in acidity, making it significantly harder for shellfish to build calcium carbonate shells": "",
  "Marine organisms can tolerate pH fluctuations of up to 1.0 units without experiencing adverse effects, so a 0.1 change is well within their tolerance": "",
  "The pH scale is logarithmic, so a drop of 0.1 units represents about a 30% increase in hydrogen ion concentration (acidity), which significantly reduces the availability of carbonate ions that shellfish need for shells.": "",
